<div class="highlight"><pre><span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">wtfmate</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">humanname</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="sd">&quot;&quot;&quot;converts user input into string look up code. You can give it &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
    <span class="k">try</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">humanname</span> <span class="o">==</span><span class="s">&quot;1&quot;</span> <span class="ow">or</span> <span class="n">humanname</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="mi">1</span> <span class="ow">or</span> <span class="n">humanname</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="s">&quot;GSWS01&quot;</span><span class="p">:</span>

        <span class="k">elif</span> <span class="n">humanname</span> <span class="o">==</span><span class="s">&quot;6&quot;</span> <span class="ow">or</span> <span class="n">humanname</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="mi">6</span> <span class="ow">or</span> <span class="n">humanname</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="s">&quot;GSWS06&quot;</span><span class="p">:</span>

            <span class="n">wsnum</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s">&quot;GSWS07&quot;</span>
        <span class="k">elif</span> <span class="n">humanname</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="s">&quot;8&quot;</span> <span class="ow">or</span> <span class="n">humanname</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="mi">8</span> <span class="ow">or</span> <span class="n">humanname</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="s">&quot;GSWS08&quot;</span><span class="p">:</span>

        <span class="k">elif</span> <span class="n">humanname</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="s">&quot;cc02&quot;</span> <span class="ow">or</span> <span class="n">humanname</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="s">&quot;CC02&quot;</span> <span class="ow">or</span> <span class="n">humanname</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="s">&quot;GSCC02&quot;</span><span class="p">:</span>
            <span class="n">wsnum</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s">&quot;GSCC02&quot;</span>
        <span class="k">elif</span> <span class="n">humanname</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="s">&quot;cc03&quot;</span> <span class="ow">or</span> <span class="n">humanname</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="s">&quot;CC03&quot;</span> <span class="ow">or</span> <span class="n">humanname</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="s">&quot;GSCC03&quot;</span><span class="p">:</span>
            <span class="n">wsnum</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s">&quot;GSCC03&quot;</span>
        <span class="k">elif</span> <span class="n">humanname</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="s">&quot;cc04&quot;</span> <span class="ow">or</span> <span class="n">humanname</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="s">&quot;CC04&quot;</span> <span class="ow">or</span> <span class="n">humanname</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="s">&quot;GSCC04&quot;</span><span class="p">:</span>
            <span class="n">wsnum</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s">&quot;GSCC04&quot;</span>
        <span class="k">else</span><span class="p">:</span>
            <span class="n">wsnum</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">humanname</span>

    <span class="k">except</span> <span class="ne">ValueError</span><span class="p">:</span>

        <span class="k">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s">&quot;The watershed name should be either the integer of the watershed in double-quotes or it&#39;s six-character name, such as GSWS01, also in double-quotes. For Coyote, we accept the forms of CC01 or GSCC01. For Mack, we accept mack, MACK, GSWSMA, GSMACK and for fish we accept fish, FISH, and GSWSMF&quot;</span><span class="p">)</span>

    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">wsnum</span>
</pre></div>

<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>The corr tables are created by Craig, or found in the HF004 db drive. One thing Craig and I discussed a while back was doing the corr tables by year and watershed, and in a way he could open them in Excel. This made good sense to me and it was easier for him. The naming convention is &quot;corr<em>table_lower case watershed name \</em> wateryear.csv&quot;. The function matches the table with the name and year.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">
In&nbsp;[8]:
</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class="highlight"><pre><span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">getcorrtable</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">wateryear</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">wsnum</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="sd">&quot;&quot;&quot; corr table must be present and named corr_table_wsname_year.csv </span>
<span class="sd">    for example, corr_table_gscc01_2014.csv</span>
<span class="sd">    corr_table_gsws01_2015.csv</span>
<span class="sd">    etc.</span>
<span class="sd">    &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
    <span class="n">s</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">wsnum</span>

    <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">wateryear</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="s">&quot;2014&quot;</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="n">corr</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s">&quot;corr_table_&quot;</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">s</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">lower</span><span class="p">()</span><span class="o">+</span><span class="s">&quot;_&quot;</span><span class="o">+</span><span class="s">&quot;2014.csv&quot;</span>
    <span class="k">elif</span> <span class="n">wateryear</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="s">&quot;2015&quot;</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="n">corr</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s">&quot;corr_table_&quot;</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">s</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">lower</span><span class="p">()</span><span class="o">+</span><span class="s">&quot;_&quot;</span><span class="o">+</span><span class="s">&quot;2015.csv&quot;</span>
    <span class="k">elif</span> <span class="n">wateryear</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="s">&quot;2013&quot;</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="n">corr</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s">&quot;corr_table_&quot;</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">s</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">lower</span><span class="p">()</span><span class="o">+</span><span class="s">&quot;_&quot;</span><span class="o">+</span><span class="s">&quot;2013.csv&quot;</span>
    <span class="k">elif</span> <span class="n">wateryear</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="s">&quot;2012&quot;</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="n">corr</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s">&quot;corr_table_&quot;</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">s</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">lower</span><span class="p">()</span><span class="o">+</span><span class="s">&quot;_&quot;</span><span class="o">+</span><span class="s">&quot;2012.csv&quot;</span>
    <span class="k">elif</span> <span class="n">wateryear</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="s">&quot;2011&quot;</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="n">corr</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s">&quot;corr_table_&quot;</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">s</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">lower</span><span class="p">()</span><span class="o">+</span><span class="s">&quot;_&quot;</span><span class="o">+</span><span class="s">&quot;2011.csv&quot;</span>
    <span class="k">elif</span> <span class="n">wateryear</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="s">&quot;2010&quot;</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="n">corr</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s">&quot;corr_table_&quot;</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">s</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">lower</span><span class="p">()</span><span class="o">+</span><span class="s">&quot;_&quot;</span><span class="o">+</span><span class="s">&quot;2010.csv&quot;</span>
    <span class="k">else</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="n">corr</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s">&quot;corr_table_2013.csv&quot;</span>

    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">corr</span>
</pre></div>

<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>One thing I wish I knew when I began coding was that computers know both way more and way less about dates than humans do. Or, to put it simpler, computers are really good about keeping track of dates, and humans are really good about intuiting what a date string might mean. Case in point, we define a few date formats outright in the main loop that we use a lot so that it&#39;s less of a hassle to write exception handlers on every single date stamp. </p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">
In&nbsp;[10]:
</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class="highlight"><pre><span class="c">### set the dateformat(s) here in the program </span>
<span class="c">## -- if you need new date formats you may need to add them in later</span>
<span class="c"># in general, Craig favors the one on top, but most other people like the one on bottom</span>

<span class="n">dateformat</span>  <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s">&#39;%m/</span><span class="si">%d</span><span class="s">/%Y %H:%M&#39;</span>
<span class="n">dateformat2</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s">&#39;%Y-%m-</span><span class="si">%d</span><span class="s"> %H:%M:%S&#39;</span>
</pre></div>

</div>
</div>
</div>

</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">
In&nbsp;[11]:
</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class="highlight"><pre><span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">convert_corr_to_dict</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">filename</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">wsnum</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="sd">&quot;&quot;&quot; </span>
<span class="sd">    this was the first time I ever used a dictionary explicitly.</span>
<span class="sd">    it takes an input of the filename, which remember is the corr table,</span>
<span class="sd">    and the watershed number, like gsws08, or gscc01</span>
<span class="sd">    and it output is a version of the corr table that can be referenced by date stamp</span>
<span class="sd">    &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>

    <span class="n">reader</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">csv</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">reader</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">open</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">filename</span><span class="p">))</span>
    
    <span class="n">d</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">{}</span>

    <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">row</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">reader</span><span class="p">:</span>
        
        <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">row</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="n">wsnum</span><span class="p">:</span>
            <span class="k">try</span><span class="p">:</span>
                <span class="n">dt</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">datetime</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">datetime</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">strptime</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">row</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">3</span><span class="p">],</span><span class="n">dateformat</span><span class="p">)</span>
            <span class="k">except</span> <span class="ne">Exception</span><span class="p">:</span>
                <span class="n">dt</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">datetime</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">datetime</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">strptime</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">row</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">3</span><span class="p">],</span><span class="n">dateformat2</span><span class="p">)</span>

            <span class="n">dt</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">dt</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="n">datetime</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">timedelta</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">minutes</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">dt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">minute</span> <span class="o">%</span> <span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">)</span>

<p>Over time we have had many names for the files that went into this program. When I first started, all I had was PORTAL, and the files were broken up into many separate parts with unknown starts and ends. Date columns came, and date columns left. Files were concatenated, and files were broken apart. Values were duplicated, missing, mutated, and shifted off par. We got the .csvs finally from the internet in a complete way, only to discover Craig&#39;s computer would break when handling them. So I wrote some quick awk stuff to just get what I needed by piping some command line stuff through. Of course then the files changed again. People grew old, died, or retired. MATLAB decided to not like its own Java driver. Python was still better. Small alien spaceships landed on earth and Emilio Estevez and Will Smith flew up to greet them only to discover that the threat to our planet was, in fact, using Windows. Finally, we came to the stage where we gave up and said, crap on it, just put the damn file names in the program. And that is exactly what we did.</p>

<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>The date checker function was recently added to deal with the fact that the incoming data may not always be five-minute gap filled data. After investigating the method I had before, I determined that I was relying on the way I had built the files I downloaded to be fully gap filled to five minutes on the date stamps. This was a mistake on my part that would not be safe in the future. So adding the date checker function preserves the old structure while at the same time creating a gap-filled version of the raw data for replacement, if needed.</p>
</div>

<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">
In&nbsp;[17]:
</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class="highlight"><pre><span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">drange</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">start</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">stop</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">step</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="sd">&quot;&quot;&quot; fraction/date range generator &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
    <span class="n">r</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">start</span>
    <span class="k">while</span> <span class="n">r</span> <span class="o">&lt;</span> <span class="n">stop</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="k">yield</span> <span class="n">r</span>
        <span class="n">r</span> <span class="o">+=</span> <span class="n">step</span>

<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">date_checker</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">wateryear</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">wsnum</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="sd">&quot;&quot;&quot; new function added by Fox 08-03-2015 </span>
<span class="sd">    - this will check for gaps in the date series </span>
<span class="sd">    and create a filled source</span>
<span class="sd">    &quot;&quot;&quot;</span>
    <span class="n">firstval</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">datetime</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">datetime</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">int</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">wateryear</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">10</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">lastval</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">datetime</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">datetime</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">int</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">wateryear</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="mi">10</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">dur</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">datetime</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">timedelta</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">minutes</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">ideal</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">drange</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">firstval</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">lastval</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">dur</span><span class="p">)</span>

    <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">wsnum</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="s">&quot;GSCC01&quot;</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="nb">file</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">cc01</span>
    <span class="k">elif</span> <span class="n">wsnum</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="s">&quot;GSCC02&quot;</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="nb">file</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">cc02</span>
    <span class="k">elif</span> <span class="n">wsnum</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="s">&quot;GSCC03&quot;</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="nb">file</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">cc03</span>
    <span class="k">elif</span> <span class="n">wsnum</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="s">&quot;GSCC04&quot;</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="nb">file</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">cc04</span>
    <span class="k">elif</span> <span class="n">wsnum</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="s">&quot;GSWS09&quot;</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="nb">file</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">ws9</span>
    <span class="k">elif</span> <span class="n">wsnum</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="s">&quot;GSWS01&quot;</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="nb">file</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">ws1</span>
    <span class="k">elif</span> <span class="n">wsnum</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="s">&quot;GSWS02&quot;</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="nb">file</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">ws2</span>
    <span class="k">elif</span> <span class="n">wsnum</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="s">&quot;GSWS03&quot;</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="nb">file</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">ws3</span>
    <span class="k">elif</span> <span class="n">wsnum</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="s">&quot;GSWS06&quot;</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="nb">file</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">ws6</span>
    <span class="k">elif</span> <span class="n">wsnum</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="s">&quot;GSWS07&quot;</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="nb">file</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">ws7</span>
    <span class="k">elif</span> <span class="n">wsnum</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="s">&quot;GSWS08&quot;</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="nb">file</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">ws8</span>
    <span class="k">elif</span> <span class="n">wsnum</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="s">&quot;GSWSMA&quot;</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="nb">file</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">wsmack</span>
    <span class="k">elif</span> <span class="n">wsnum</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="s">&quot;GSWSMF&quot;</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="nb">file</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">wsfish</span>
    <span class="k">elif</span> <span class="n">wsnum</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="s">&quot;GSWS10&quot;</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="nb">file</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">ws10</span>
    <span class="k">else</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="k">print</span> <span class="s">&quot;we don&#39;t know how to process that file yet&quot;</span>
    <span class="n">thefileref</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">file</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">]</span>

    <span class="n">mytime</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="n">x</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">x</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">ideal</span><span class="p">]</span>

    <span class="n">save_rows</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[]</span>
    <span class="k">with</span> <span class="nb">open</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">thefileref</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s">&#39;rb&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="n">readfile</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="n">reader</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">csv</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">reader</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">readfile</span><span class="p">)</span>

        <span class="n">od</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">{}</span>

        
        <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">row</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">reader</span><span class="p">:</span>
            <span class="n">dt</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">datetime</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">datetime</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">strptime</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">str</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">row</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">]),</span> <span class="s">&#39;%Y-%m-</span><span class="si">%d</span><span class="s"> %H:%M:%S&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>

            <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">dt</span> <span class="o">&lt;</span> <span class="n">firstval</span><span class="p">:</span>
                <span class="k">continue</span>

            <span class="k">try</span><span class="p">:</span>
                <span class="n">initialval</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">round</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">float</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">str</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">row</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">])),</span><span class="mi">3</span><span class="p">)</span>
            <span class="k">except</span> <span class="ne">Exception</span><span class="p">:</span>
                <span class="n">initialval</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="bp">None</span>

            <span class="k">try</span><span class="p">:</span>
                <span class="n">adjval</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">round</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">float</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">str</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">row</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">])),</span><span class="mi">3</span><span class="p">)</span>
            <span class="k">except</span> <span class="ne">Exception</span><span class="p">:</span>
                <span class="n">adjval</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="bp">None</span>

            <span class="k">try</span><span class="p">:</span>
                <span class="n">flag</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">str</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">row</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">3</span><span class="p">])</span>
            <span class="k">except</span> <span class="ne">Exception</span><span class="p">:</span>
                <span class="n">flag</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s">&quot;Q&quot;</span>

            <span class="k">try</span><span class="p">:</span>
                <span class="n">event</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">str</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">row</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">4</span><span class="p">])</span>
            <span class="k">except</span> <span class="ne">Exception</span><span class="p">:</span>
                <span class="n">event</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s">&quot;NA&quot;</span>


            <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">dt</span> <span class="ow">not</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">od</span><span class="p">:</span>
                <span class="n">od</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">dt</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">{</span><span class="s">&#39;init&#39;</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="n">initialval</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s">&#39;adj&#39;</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="n">adjval</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s">&#39;flag&#39;</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="n">flag</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s">&#39;event&#39;</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="n">event</span><span class="p">}</span>
            <span class="k">elif</span> <span class="n">dt</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">od</span><span class="p">:</span>
                <span class="k">print</span> <span class="s">&quot;duplicate at &quot;</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">datetime</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">datetime</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">strftime</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">dt</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s">&#39;%Y-%m-</span><span class="si">%d</span><span class="s"> %H:%M:%S&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>


        <span class="c"># number of data points missing in total</span>
        <span class="n">all_good</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">0</span>

        <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">each_check</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">mytime</span><span class="p">:</span>



            <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">each_check</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">od</span><span class="p">:</span>
                <span class="n">most_recent</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">od</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">each_check</span><span class="p">]</span>
                <span class="n">save_rows</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="n">datetime</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">datetime</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">strftime</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">each_check</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s">&#39;%Y-%m-</span><span class="si">%d</span><span class="s"> %H:%M:%S&#39;</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="n">od</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">each_check</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="s">&#39;init&#39;</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">od</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">each_check</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="s">&#39;adj&#39;</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">od</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">each_check</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="s">&#39;flag&#39;</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">od</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">each_check</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="s">&#39;event&#39;</span><span class="p">]])</span>
                <span class="k">pass</span>

            <span class="k">elif</span> <span class="n">each_check</span> <span class="ow">not</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">od</span><span class="p">:</span>
                
                <span class="n">save_rows</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="n">datetime</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">datetime</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">strftime</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">each_check</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s">&#39;%Y-%m-</span><span class="si">%d</span><span class="s"> %H:%M:%S&#39;</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="n">most_recent</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s">&#39;init&#39;</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">most_recent</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s">&#39;adj&#39;</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">most_recent</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s">&#39;flag&#39;</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">most_recent</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s">&#39;event&#39;</span><span class="p">]])</span>
        
                <span class="n">all_good</span> <span class="o">+=</span><span class="mi">1</span>

        <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">all_good</span> <span class="o">&gt;</span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">:</span>
            <span class="k">print</span> <span class="s">&quot;there are &quot;</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="nb">str</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">all_good</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="s">&quot; missing five minute periods, so ...&quot;</span>
            <span class="k">print</span> <span class="s">&quot;We will initiate from filled file. This file is found as salvage_time_watershednumber_wateryear.csv&quot;</span>
            <span class="k">print</span> <span class="s">&quot;The rest of your processing will be normal :)&quot;</span>

    <span class="n">filename</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s">&quot;salvage_time_&quot;</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">wsnum</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="s">&quot;_&quot;</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="nb">str</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">wateryear</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="s">&quot;.csv&quot;</span>
    
    <span class="k">with</span> <span class="nb">open</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">filename</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s">&#39;wb&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="n">writefile</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="n">writer</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">csv</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">writer</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">writefile</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">quoting</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">csv</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">QUOTE_NONNUMERIC</span><span class="p">)</span>

        <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">each_item</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">save_rows</span><span class="p">:</span>
            <span class="n">writer</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">writerow</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">each_item</span><span class="p">)</span>

    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">all_good</span>
</pre></div>

<div class="highlight"><pre><span class="c"># to launch the main loop - this time on saved inputs and ws9, coyote, etc.</span>
<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">lockandload</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">thefile</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">thedate</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">theoutput</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">thedata</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">od</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">wateryear</span><span class="p">,</span>
           <span class="n">beginRatio</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="bp">None</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">beginRatioScale</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="bp">None</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">endRatio</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="bp">None</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">endRatioScale</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="bp">None</span><span class="p">,</span>
           <span class="n">countmeas</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="bp">None</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">lastTime</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="bp">None</span><span class="p">):</span>

    <span class="k">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s">&quot; original file ~&gt; &quot;</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="nb">str</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">thefile</span><span class="p">))</span>
    <span class="k">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s">&quot; output file ~&gt; &quot;</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="nb">str</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">theoutput</span><span class="p">))</span>

    <span class="c"># open the file and read it</span>
    <span class="k">with</span> <span class="nb">open</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">thefile</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s">&#39;r&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="n">csvfile</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="n">reader</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">csv</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">reader</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">csvfile</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">delimiter</span> <span class="o">=</span><span class="s">&quot;,&quot;</span><span class="p">)</span>

        <span class="c"># these are the values and times we have </span>
        <span class="n">existing_values</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[]</span>
        <span class="n">existing_times</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[]</span>

        <span class="c"># this is the new values that are adjusted</span>
        <span class="n">result</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[]</span>

        <span class="c"># this is the flags we have assigned</span>
        <span class="n">flags</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[]</span>

        <span class="c"># this is the event matches</span>
        <span class="n">events</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[]</span>

        <span class="c"># open an output file which we&#39;ll write the time series to once adjusted</span>
        <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">beginRatio</span> <span class="ow">is</span> <span class="bp">None</span><span class="p">:</span>
            <span class="n">writemode</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s">&quot;w&quot;</span>
        <span class="k">else</span><span class="p">:</span>
            <span class="n">writemode</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s">&quot;a&quot;</span>

        <span class="k">with</span> <span class="nb">open</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">theoutput</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">writemode</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="n">outfile</span><span class="p">:</span>

            <span class="n">writer</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">csv</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">writer</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">outfile</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">quoting</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">csv</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">QUOTE_NONNUMERIC</span><span class="p">)</span>

            <span class="c"># in the first step the ratios are 1 because the relationship between hg and cr is same</span>
            <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">beginRatio</span> <span class="ow">is</span> <span class="bp">None</span><span class="p">:</span>
                <span class="n">beginRatio</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mf">1.0</span>
            <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">beginRatioScale</span> <span class="ow">is</span> <span class="bp">None</span><span class="p">:</span>
                <span class="n">beginRatioScale</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mf">1.0</span>
            <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">endRatio</span> <span class="ow">is</span> <span class="bp">None</span><span class="p">:</span>
                <span class="n">endRatio</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mf">0.0</span>
            <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">endRatioScale</span> <span class="ow">is</span> <span class="bp">None</span><span class="p">:</span>
                <span class="n">endRatioScale</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mf">0.0</span>
            <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">countmeas</span> <span class="ow">is</span> <span class="bp">None</span><span class="p">:</span>
                <span class="n">countmeas</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">0</span> 

            <span class="c"># start with the first row</span>
            <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">row</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">reader</span><span class="p">:</span>

                <span class="c"># define the current date time</span>
                <span class="n">dt</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">row</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">thedate</span><span class="p">]</span>

                <span class="c"># format the current date time </span>
                <span class="k">try</span><span class="p">:</span>
                    <span class="n">dt</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">datetime</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">datetime</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">strptime</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">row</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">thedate</span><span class="p">],</span><span class="n">dateformat</span><span class="p">)</span>

                <span class="k">except</span> <span class="ne">Exception</span><span class="p">:</span>

                    <span class="n">dt</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">datetime</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">datetime</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">strptime</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">row</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">thedate</span><span class="p">],</span><span class="n">dateformat2</span><span class="p">)</span>

                <span class="c"># skip over the stuff which is not really in this table</span>
                <span class="k">if</span> <span class="nb">int</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">wateryear</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">1</span> <span class="o">&gt;=</span> <span class="n">dt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">year</span> <span class="ow">and</span> <span class="n">dt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">month</span> <span class="o">&lt;</span> <span class="mi">9</span><span class="p">:</span>
                    <span class="k">continue</span>
                <span class="k">else</span><span class="p">:</span>
                    <span class="k">pass</span>      

                <span class="c"># if you are putting two files together, make sure you start at the last one...</span>
                <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">lastTime</span> <span class="ow">is</span> <span class="ow">not</span> <span class="bp">None</span><span class="p">:</span>

                    <span class="k">try</span><span class="p">:</span>
                        <span class="n">lastTime</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">datetime</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">datetime</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">strptime</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">lastTime</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">dateformat</span><span class="p">)</span>
                    <span class="k">except</span> <span class="n">exception</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="n">Exc</span><span class="p">:</span>
                        <span class="n">lastTime</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">datetime</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">datetime</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">strptime</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">lastTime</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">dateformat2</span><span class="p">)</span>

                    <span class="k">print</span> <span class="n">lastTime</span>

                    <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">dt</span> <span class="o">&lt;=</span> <span class="n">lastTime</span><span class="p">:</span>
                        <span class="k">continue</span>

                <span class="c"># format the current date time</span>
                <span class="n">thistime</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">str</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">dt</span><span class="p">)</span>

                <span class="c"># define a five minute step</span>
                <span class="n">step</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">datetime</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">timedelta</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">minutes</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">)</span>

                <span class="c"># if there aren&#39;t yet any values in the list</span>
                <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">existing_values</span><span class="o">==</span><span class="p">[]:</span>

                    <span class="c"># define what the next time should be</span>
                    <span class="n">nexttimeshouldbe</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">dt</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">step</span>
                    
                    <span class="c"># the real value is the cr value in the data</span>
                    <span class="n">realvalue</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">float</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">row</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">thedata</span><span class="p">])</span>

                    <span class="c"># the adjusted value is the same since we&#39;re in the first step</span>
                    <span class="n">adjustedvalue</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">float</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">row</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">thedata</span><span class="p">])</span>

                    <span class="c"># append to the existing times the time right now</span>
                    <span class="n">existing_times</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">thistime</span><span class="p">)</span>

                    <span class="c"># append to the existing values the real value</span>
                    <span class="n">existing_values</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">realvalue</span><span class="p">)</span>

                    <span class="c"># append to results the results</span>
                    <span class="n">result</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">adjustedvalue</span><span class="p">)</span>

                    <span class="k">try</span><span class="p">:</span> 
                        <span class="n">thisflag</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">str</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">row</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">3</span><span class="p">])</span>
                    <span class="k">except</span> <span class="ne">Exception</span><span class="p">:</span>
                        <span class="n">thisflag</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s">&quot;A&quot;</span>
                        <span class="k">print</span> <span class="s">&quot;flag assigned as A&quot;</span>

                    <span class="n">flags</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">thisflag</span><span class="p">)</span>

                    <span class="c"># first event is not anything</span>
                    <span class="n">thisevent</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s">&quot;NA&quot;</span>

                    <span class="n">events</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">thisevent</span><span class="p">)</span>

                    <span class="c"># write the time as a string and the values as a string and the adjusted values as strings also</span>
                    <span class="n">writer</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">writerow</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="nb">str</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">thistime</span><span class="p">),</span><span class="nb">str</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">realvalue</span><span class="p">),</span><span class="nb">str</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">adjustedvalue</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="n">thisflag</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">thisevent</span><span class="p">])</span>
                
                <span class="c"># after the first step the existing values will not be emtpy, and the  </span>
                <span class="c"># subsequent time and this one are the same   </span>
                <span class="k">elif</span> <span class="n">existing_values</span><span class="o">!=</span> <span class="p">[]:</span>

                    <span class="c">###</span>
                    <span class="c"># new? ! ?</span>
                    <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">dt</span> <span class="o">!=</span> <span class="n">nexttimeshouldbe</span><span class="p">:</span>
                        <span class="k">print</span> <span class="s">&quot;dates aren&#39;t ok; something is missing. Program is exiting on:&quot;</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">datetime</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">datetime</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">strftime</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">dt</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s">&#39;%Y-%m-</span><span class="si">%d</span><span class="s"> %H:%M:%S&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>
                        <span class="k">print</span> <span class="s">&quot;please make appropriate corrections. Press CTRL + C or type quit() to stop the shell and fix your data&quot;</span>
                        <span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">pdb</span><span class="p">;</span> <span class="n">pdb</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_trace</span><span class="p">()</span>

                    <span class="c"># if there is an adjustment happening</span>
                    <span class="k">if</span> <span class="nb">str</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">dt</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">od1</span><span class="p">:</span>
                        
                        <span class="n">countmeas</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">0</span>

                        <span class="c"># the beginning ratio is the weight of the hg/cr at time 1</span>
                        <span class="n">beginRatio</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">float</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">od1</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="nb">str</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">dt</span><span class="p">)][</span><span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">])</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="nb">float</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">od1</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="nb">str</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">dt</span><span class="p">)][</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">])</span> <span class="c"># HG/CR</span>

                        <span class="c"># the ending ratio is the weight of the hg/cr at time 2</span>
                        <span class="k">try</span><span class="p">:</span>
                            <span class="n">endRatio</span>   <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">float</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">od1</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="nb">str</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">dt</span><span class="p">)][</span><span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">])</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="nb">float</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">od1</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="nb">str</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">dt</span><span class="p">)][</span><span class="mi">4</span><span class="p">])</span> <span class="c"># HG/CR</span>
                        <span class="k">except</span> <span class="ne">Exception</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="n">exc</span><span class="p">:</span>
                            <span class="n">endRatio</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">beginRatio</span>

                        <span class="c"># the next check gets the end of the period over which these ratios are relevant</span>
                        <span class="k">try</span><span class="p">:</span>
                            <span class="n">nextcheck</span>  <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">datetime</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">datetime</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">strptime</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">od1</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="nb">str</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">dt</span><span class="p">)][</span><span class="mi">3</span><span class="p">],</span><span class="n">dateformat</span><span class="p">)</span>
                        <span class="k">except</span> <span class="ne">Exception</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="n">exc</span><span class="p">:</span>
                            <span class="n">boundary</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">str</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">wateryear</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="s">&quot;-09-30 23:55:00&quot;</span>
                            <span class="n">nextcheck</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">datetime</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">datetime</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">strptime</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">boundary</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">dateformat2</span><span class="p">)</span>
                            <span class="c">#nextcheck = datetime.datetime.strptime(&quot;2014-09-30 23:55:00&quot;,dateformat2)</span>
                        
                        <span class="c"># the difference of time is the number of steps</span>
                        <span class="n">difftime</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">nextcheck</span> <span class="o">-</span> <span class="n">dt</span> <span class="c"># number of steps to next interval</span>
                            
                        <span class="c"># number of days different*24hoursinday*60minsinhour/5mins + </span>
                        <span class="c"># number of hours different*60minutesinhour/5mins + minutes modulo 5</span>
                        <span class="c"># some of the intervals will be off so we just use the preceding interval</span>
                        <span class="n">numsteps</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">difftime</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">days</span><span class="o">*</span><span class="mi">24</span><span class="o">*</span><span class="mi">60</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="mf">5.0</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">difftime</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">seconds</span><span class="o">//</span><span class="mi">60</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="mf">5.0</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="p">((</span><span class="n">difftime</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">seconds</span><span class="o">//</span><span class="mi">60</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">%</span><span class="k">60</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">%</span><span class="k">5</span>
                        <span class="n">beginRatioScale</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="mf">1.0</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="n">countmeas</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="n">numsteps</span><span class="p">)</span>
                        <span class="n">endRatioScale</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">countmeas</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="n">numsteps</span>
                        <span class="c"># the slope is the change between cr and hg over which we&#39; weight the observations</span>
                        <span class="n">slope</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">endRatio</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="n">beginRatio</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="n">numsteps</span>
                        
                        <span class="n">thisevent</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s">&quot;MAINTE&quot;</span>
                        <span class="k">try</span><span class="p">:</span>
                            <span class="n">thisflag</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">str</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">row</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">3</span><span class="p">])</span>
                        <span class="k">except</span> <span class="ne">Exception</span><span class="p">:</span>
                            <span class="n">thisflag</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s">&quot;A&quot;</span>
                            <span class="k">print</span> <span class="s">&quot;flag defaults to A&quot;</span>

                    <span class="k">else</span><span class="p">:</span>
                        <span class="k">try</span><span class="p">:</span>
                            <span class="n">thisflag</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">str</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">row</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">3</span><span class="p">])</span>
                        <span class="k">except</span> <span class="ne">Exception</span><span class="p">:</span>
                            <span class="n">thisflag</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s">&quot;A&quot;</span>
                            <span class="k">print</span> <span class="s">&quot;flag defaults to A&quot;</span>
                        <span class="n">thisevent</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s">&#39;NA&#39;</span>     

                    <span class="c"># move the next time to the next time</span>
                    <span class="n">nexttimeshouldbe</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">dt</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">step</span>
                    
                    <span class="c"># append to the existing times the data from the time you measure</span>
                    <span class="n">existing_times</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">thistime</span><span class="p">)</span>
                    <span class="k">try</span><span class="p">:</span>
                        <span class="c"># append to the existing values the new value</span>
                        <span class="n">realvalue</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">float</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">row</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">thedata</span><span class="p">])</span>
                    
                    <span class="k">except</span> <span class="ne">Exception</span><span class="p">:</span>
                        <span class="k">print</span> <span class="n">row</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">thedata</span><span class="p">]</span>
                        
                    <span class="n">existing_values</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">realvalue</span><span class="p">)</span>

                    <span class="c"># compute the adjusted value</span>
                    <span class="n">adjustedvalue</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">float</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">row</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">thedata</span><span class="p">])</span><span class="o">*</span><span class="n">beginRatio</span><span class="o">*</span><span class="n">beginRatioScale</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="nb">float</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">row</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">thedata</span><span class="p">])</span><span class="o">*</span><span class="n">endRatio</span><span class="o">*</span><span class="n">endRatioScale</span>
                    
                    <span class="c"># add 1 to the measurement count </span>
                    <span class="n">result</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">adjustedvalue</span><span class="p">)</span>

                    <span class="c"># mark that flag as &quot;A&quot;</span>
                    <span class="c"># try:</span>
                    <span class="c">#     this_flag = str(row[3])</span>
                    <span class="c"># except Exception:</span>
                    <span class="c">#     print &quot;exception thrown?&quot;</span>
                    <span class="c">#     import pdb; pdb.set_trace()</span>
                    <span class="c">#     thisflag = &quot;A&quot;</span>
                    
                    <span class="n">flags</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">thisflag</span><span class="p">)</span>

                    <span class="n">events</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">thisevent</span><span class="p">)</span>
                    <span class="n">countmeas</span> <span class="o">+=</span> <span class="mi">1</span>

                    <span class="c">#print result</span>
                    <span class="n">writer</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">writerow</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="nb">str</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">thistime</span><span class="p">),</span><span class="nb">str</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">realvalue</span><span class="p">),</span><span class="nb">str</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">adjustedvalue</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="n">thisflag</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">thisevent</span><span class="p">])</span>
                
                <span class="k">else</span><span class="p">:</span>

                    <span class="c"># if the date is missing, then append to the times the missing date time </span>
                    <span class="c"># for example, if it&#39;s coyote creek and today is like 10-10-2010 01:00:00 and </span>
                    <span class="c"># next time is 10:11:2010 02:00:00, we add the next time but give it the current values</span>
                    <span class="c"># because we assume &quot;no change&quot;</span>
                    <span class="n">existing_times</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">nexttimeshouldbe</span><span class="p">)</span>

                    <span class="c"># a temporary storage of the current computed dt</span>
                    <span class="n">temp</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">nexttimeshouldbe</span>
                    <span class="c"># compute the next time subsequent to this one</span>
                    <span class="n">nexttimeshouldbe</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">temp</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">step</span>
                    <span class="c"># the &quot;real value&quot; is the previous real value</span>
                    <span class="n">existing_values</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">realvalue</span><span class="p">)</span> 
                    <span class="c"># say that the adjusted value is actually the same as the previous adjusted value</span>
                    <span class="n">adjustedvalue</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">realvalue</span><span class="o">*</span><span class="n">beginRatio</span><span class="o">*</span><span class="n">beginRatioScale</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">realvalue</span><span class="o">*</span><span class="n">endRatio</span><span class="o">*</span><span class="n">endRatioScale</span>
                    <span class="c"># continue the count</span>
                    <span class="n">result</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">adjustedvalue</span><span class="p">)</span>

                    <span class="n">thisflag</span> <span class="o">=</span><span class="s">&quot;M&quot;</span>
                    <span class="n">thisevent</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s">&quot;Missing Value&quot;</span>
                    <span class="n">flags</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">thisflag</span><span class="p">)</span>
                    <span class="n">events</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">append</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">thisevent</span><span class="p">)</span>
                    <span class="n">countmeas</span> <span class="o">+=</span><span class="mi">1</span>
                    <span class="n">writer</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">writerow</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="nb">str</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">thistime</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="bp">None</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="bp">None</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">thisflag</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">thisevent</span><span class="p">])</span>

    <span class="c">#import pdb; pdb.set_trace()</span>
    <span class="n">final_parameters</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">{</span>
        <span class="s">&quot;beginRatio&quot;</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="n">beginRatio</span><span class="p">,</span>
        <span class="s">&quot;beginRatioScale&quot;</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="n">beginRatioScale</span><span class="p">,</span>
        <span class="s">&quot;endRatio&quot;</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="n">endRatio</span><span class="p">,</span>
        <span class="s">&quot;endRatioScale&quot;</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="n">endRatioScale</span><span class="p">,</span>
        <span class="s">&quot;countmeas&quot;</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="n">countmeas</span><span class="p">,</span>
        <span class="s">&quot;lastTime&quot;</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="n">existing_times</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">],</span>
    <span class="p">}</span>
    <span class="k">return</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">existing_times</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">existing_values</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">result</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">flags</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">events</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">final_parameters</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>

</div>

<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>The functions below are used to create the back up copies of the adjusted data. This allows at least one level of &quot;undo&quot; if a change was made that was not desireable. Because some of the incoming data may not have flags or events in them (at least in the Portal versions from 2013 we originally had), there are 2 methods -- the default is to look for flags and events, the fallback is to not look for them.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">
In&nbsp;[24]:
</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class="highlight"><pre><span class="n">existing_times</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">existing_values</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">result</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">flags</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">events</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">final_parameters</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">lockandload</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">thefile</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">thedate</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">theoutput</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">thedata</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">od1</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">wateryear</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>

</div>

<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">
In&nbsp;[25]:
</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class="highlight"><pre><span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">copyfile</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">mynum</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">wateryear</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">existing_times</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">existing_values</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">result</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">flags</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">events</span><span class="p">):</span>

    <span class="c"># use on portal ws with flags</span>
    <span class="n">name_copyfile</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s">&quot;copyof_wy&quot;</span><span class="o">+</span><span class="n">wateryear</span><span class="o">+</span><span class="s">&#39;_&#39;</span><span class="o">+</span><span class="n">mynum</span><span class="o">+</span><span class="s">&quot;.csv&quot;</span>
    <span class="k">with</span> <span class="nb">open</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">name_copyfile</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s">&#39;w&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="n">outfile</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="n">writer</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">csv</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">writer</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">outfile</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">quoting</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">csv</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">QUOTE_NONNUMERIC</span><span class="p">)</span>

        <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">item1</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">item2</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">item3</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">item4</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">item5</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">zip</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">existing_times</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">existing_values</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">result</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">flags</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">events</span><span class="p">):</span>
            <span class="n">writer</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">writerow</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="nb">str</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">item1</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="nb">str</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">item2</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="nb">str</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">item3</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="nb">str</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">item4</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="nb">str</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">item5</span><span class="p">)])</span>
    
    <span class="k">return</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">name_copyfile</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">copyfile2</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">mynum</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">wateryear</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">existing_times</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">existing_values</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">result</span><span class="p">):</span>

    <span class="c"># use on data logger WS with no flags</span>
    <span class="n">name_copyfile</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="s">&quot;copyof_wy&quot;</span><span class="o">+</span><span class="n">wateryear</span><span class="o">+</span><span class="s">&#39;_&#39;</span><span class="o">+</span><span class="n">mynum</span><span class="o">+</span><span class="s">&quot;.csv&quot;</span>
    <span class="k">with</span> <span class="nb">open</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">name_copyfile</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s">&#39;w&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="n">outfile</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="n">writer</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">csv</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">writer</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">outfile</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">quoting</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">csv</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">QUOTE_NONNUMERIC</span><span class="p">)</span>
        <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">item1</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">item2</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">item3</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">zip</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">existing_times</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">existing_values</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">result</span><span class="p">):</span>

<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>Lets look at one of the graphs we generated that has a spike we need to adjust.
This is a real spike/dip that happened after a maintenance event.</p>
<p>Here&#39;s the corr table entry for this event:-- the CR value of 0.97 was reset to 0.93. </p>
<pre><code>    HF002,6,GSCC01,7/10/2014 8:38,0.142,0.141,8/5/2014 6:57,0.097,0.093,
    HF002,6,GSCC01,8/5/2014 6:57,0.093,0.093,8/26/2014 7:22,0.072,0.071,
</code></pre><p>Note that this happened in between two intervals, so the next read that the CR logger has is not 0.93. Here&#39;s the data before we despike it.</p>
<pre><code>    &quot;2014-08-05 06:45:00&quot;,&quot;0.093&quot;,&quot;0.0923450704225&quot;,&quot;A&quot;,&quot;NA&quot;
    &quot;2014-08-05 06:50:00&quot;,&quot;0.093&quot;,&quot;0.0923450704225&quot;,&quot;A&quot;,&quot;NA&quot;
    &quot;2014-08-05 06:55:00&quot;,&quot;0.097&quot;,&quot;0.097&quot;,&quot;A&quot;,&quot;MAINTE&quot;
    &quot;2014-08-05 07:00:00&quot;,&quot;0.089&quot;,&quot;0.089&quot;,&quot;A&quot;,&quot;NA&quot;
    &quot;2014-08-05 07:05:00&quot;,&quot;0.094&quot;,&quot;0.094&quot;,&quot;A&quot;,&quot;NA&quot;
</code></pre><p>See how on the MAINTE event there is a jump to 0.97 and then a dip to 0.89 (we can trust the left column as being raw from the CR logger each time we run the program. The right is the adjusted.</p>
</div>

    <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">thistime</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">month</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="mi">8</span> <span class="ow">and</span> <span class="n">thistime</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">year</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="nb">int</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">wateryear</span><span class="p">):</span>

<span class="n">matplotlib</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">pyplot</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">plot_date</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">dates2</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">augvals</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="s">&#39;b-&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>
